work.work-title: O for a thousand tongues to sing

credit.credit-words: Jesus! the name that charms our fears, That bids our sorrows cease; 'Tis music in the sinner's ears, 'Tis life, and health, and peace.
O for a thousand tongues to sing
My gracious Master and my God, Assist me to proclaim, To spread through all the earth abroad The honors of Thy name.
